Male right tegmen (
Figs 54-59
)

. Stridulatory file with 67 ± 6.4 teeth (n = 6); 
mirror
: relatively conserved in this species (
Figs 61–63, 65
); however, a small cell within the second distal cell may be present (
Fig. 64
); 
harp
: one to two poorly marked diagonal veins may be present among cells or ramifying the main crossvein, in the first distal or proximal cells (
Figs 61–62, 64–65
); three to four well marked crossveins; 
basal field
: one to two vertical or diagonal crossveins can be present, forming two small cells jointed with CU 
2
(
Figs 63–64
); reticular branches can be present between the veins 1A and 2A; 

lateral field
:

with well marked accessory crossvein bifurcated (
Figs 61, 64–65
) or with many reticular veins distributed between well-marked veins (
Figs 62–63
).
